Following are major news items in Pakistani English
newspapers on Sunday. The News: -- Secretary General of the United
Nations Kofi Annan has said he would continue his effort to defuse
tensions between India and Pakistan. The Nation: -- Pakistan and
Turkmenistan underlined on Saturday the need for peace and stability in
Afghanistan and agreed to develop economic and communication links for
which peace in Afghanistan is considered a necessity. The Frontier
Post: -- The government would pay special attention to bring the
backward and underdeveloped areas on a par with the developed areas of
the country, said Mohammad Shafiq, governor of the Northwest Frontier
Province, on Saturday. Pakistan Observer: -- The Department of Food and
Agriculture has set a target of 2 million tons of wheat import for the
next fiscal year beginning July 1 this year.
